*[[1457]] &amp;ndash; [[Lorenzo Valla]], Italian humanist (b. 1406)
*[[1464]] &amp;ndash; [[Cosimo de' Medici]], Italian ruler (b. 1386)
*[[1541]] &amp;ndash; [[Simon Grynaeus]], German theologian (b. 1493)
*[[1546]] &amp;ndash; [[Peter Faber]], French theologian (b. 1506)
*[[1557]] &amp;ndash; [[Olaus Magnus]], Swedish writer (b. 1490)
*[[1580]] &amp;ndash; [[Albrecht Giese]], German politician and diplomat (b. 1524)
*[[1589]] &amp;ndash; [[Jacques Clément]], French assassin of [[Henry III of France]] (b. 1567)
*[[1675]] &amp;ndash; [[Weetamoo]], Native American noblewoman (b. 1635)
*[[1714]] &amp;ndash; [[Anne, Queen of Great Britain]] (b. 1665)
*[[1787]] &amp;ndash; [[Alphonsus Maria de Liguori]], Italian bishop, philosopher, and saint (b. 1696)
*[[1795]] &amp;ndash; [[Clas Bjerkander]], Swedish meteorologist, botanist, and entomologist (b. 1735)
*[[1796]] &amp;ndash; [[Sir Robert Pigot, 2nd Baronet]], English army officer (b. 1720)
*[[1798]] &amp;ndash; [[François-Paul Brueys d'Aigalliers]], French admiral (b. 1753)
*[[1807]] &amp;ndash; [[John Walker (lexicographer)|John Walker]], English lexicographer (b. 1732)
*[[1812]] &amp;ndash; [[Yakov Kulnev]], Russian general (b. 1763)
*[[1851]] &amp;ndash; [[William Joseph Behr]], German writer (b. 1775)
*[[1866]] &amp;ndash; [[John Ross (Cherokee chief)|John Ross]], Native American chief (b. 1790)
*[[1903]] &amp;ndash; [[Calamity Jane]], American frontier and scout (b. 1853)
*[[1911]] &amp;ndash; [[Edwin Austin Abbey]], American painter (b. 1852)
*  1911   &amp;ndash; [[Samuel Arza Davenport]], American politician (b. 1843)
*[[1917]] &amp;ndash; [[Frank Little (unionist)|Frank Little]], American labor organizer (b. 1879)
*[[1918]] &amp;ndash; [[John Riley Banister]], American cowboy and police officer (b. 1854)
*[[1920]] &amp;ndash; [[Bal Gangadhar Tilak]], Indian lawyer, reformer, and educator (b. 1856)
*[[1922]] &amp;ndash; [[Donát Bánki]], Hungarian engineer and inventor (b. 1856)
*[[1929]] &amp;ndash; [[Syd Gregory]], Australian cricketer (b. 1870)
*[[1938]] &amp;ndash; [[John Aasen]], American actor (b. 1890)
*  1938   &amp;ndash; [[Edmund C. Tarbell]], American painter (b. 1862)
*[[1943]] &amp;ndash; [[Lydia Litvyak]], Soviet pilot (b. 1921)
*[[1944]] &amp;ndash; [[Manuel L. Quezon]], Filipino politician, 2nd [[President of the Philippines]] (b. 1878)
*[[1945]] &amp;ndash; [[Gyula Csortos]], Hungarian actor (b. 1883)
*[[1966]] &amp;ndash; [[Charles Whitman]], American murderer (b. 1941)
*[[1967]] &amp;ndash; [[Richard Kuhn]], Austrian chemist, [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry|Nobel Prize]] Laureate (b. 1900)
*[[1970]] &amp;ndash; [[Frances Farmer]], American actress (b. 1913)
*  1970   &amp;ndash; [[Otto Heinrich Warburg]], German physician and physiologist, [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Nobel Prize Laureate]] (b. 1883)
*[[1973]] &amp;ndash; [[Gian Francesco Malipiero]], Italian composer (b. 1882)
*  1973   &amp;ndash; [[Walter Ulbricht]], German politician (b. 1893)
*[[1974]] &amp;ndash; [[Ildebrando Antoniutti]], Italian cardinal (b. 1898)
*[[1977]] &amp;ndash; [[Francis Gary Powers]], American pilot (b. 1929)
*[[1980]] &amp;ndash; [[Patrick Depailler]], French race car driver (b. 1944)
*  1980   &amp;ndash; [[Strother Martin]], American actor (b. 1919)
*[[1981]] &amp;ndash; [[Paddy Chayefsky]], American writer (b. 1923)
*[[1983]] &amp;ndash; [[Lilian Mercedes Letona]], Salvadoran [[guerrilla]] and activist (b. 1954)
*[[1989]] &amp;ndash; [[John Ogdon]], English pianist and composer (b. 1937)
*[[1990]] &amp;ndash; [[Norbert Elias]], German sociologist (b. 1897)
*  1990   &amp;ndash; [[Graham Young]], English serial killer (b. 1947)
*[[1996]] &amp;ndash; [[Mohamed Farrah Aidid]], Somalian general and diplomat, 5th [[President of Somalia]] (b. 1934)
*  1996   &amp;ndash; [[Frida Boccara]], French singer (b. 1940)
*  1996   &amp;ndash; [[Tadeus Reichstein]], Polish chemist, [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Nobel Prize]] Laureate (b. 1897)
*  1996   &amp;ndash; [[Lucille Teasdale-Corti]], Canadian physician (b. 1929)
*[[1997]] &amp;ndash; [[Sviatoslav Richter]], Ukrainian pianist (b. 1915)
*[[1998]] &amp;ndash; [[Eva Bartok]], Hungarian actress (b. 1927)
*[[1999]] &amp;ndash; [[Nirad C. Chaudhuri]], Bengali−English writer (b. 1897)
*[[2001]] &amp;ndash; [[Korey Stringer]], American football player (b. 1974)
*[[2003]] &amp;ndash; [[Guy Thys]], Belgian football coach (b. 1922)
*  2003   &amp;ndash; [[Marie Trintignant]], French actress (b. 1962)
*[[2004]] &amp;ndash; [[Philip Abelson]], American physicist (b. 1913)
*  2004   &amp;ndash; [[Alex Scott (Alex's Lemonade Stand)|Alexandra Scott]], American cancer patient, founder of [[Alex's Lemonade Stand]] (b. 1996)
*[[2005]] &amp;ndash; [[Al Aronowitz]], American journalist (b. 1928)
*  2005   &amp;ndash; [[Wim Boost]], Dutch cartoonist (b. 1918)
*  2005   &amp;ndash; [[Constant Nieuwenhuys]], Dutch painter (b. 1920)
*  2005   &amp;ndash; [[Fahd of Saudi Arabia]] (b. 1923)
